 :tx/rationale "Create task: CE-COGNITION: Daemon cognitive loop — autonomous structural investigation between agent requests. CONTEXT: The daemon sits idle between requests while structural questions (file existence, imports, test coverage, LOC) could be answered autonomously. Orientation scored 4.3/10 because no preparation happens. RATIONALE: Active inference requires perception + thinking + action + reflection. The daemon has all four capabilities but only uses perception (refresh). ADR-CONVERGENCE-002. APPROACH: (1) Add cognitive_tick(live, project_root, last_tick) to daemon.rs. Called every 5s in the accept loop (interleaved with connection handling). Rate-limited by last_tick. (2) Perceive: refresh_if_needed() + detect new observations since last tick via :exploration/body datom timestamp comparison. (3) Connect: for each new observation, call connect_to_existing() (CE-CONN). (4) Hypothesize: call generate_bridge_hypotheses() with temperature-adaptive params (CE-TEMP). Filter to NEW hypotheses not previously generated (dedup by source+target entity pair). (5) Self-investigate: for each bridge, extract structural checks via extract_structural_check(bridge). StructuralCheck enum: FileExists(PathBuf), ImportCheck(PathBuf, String), TestCoverage(String), LineCount(PathBuf), FunctionCount(PathBuf). investigate_structural(project_root, check) performs the check using std::fs operations and basic string matching (grep-like). Returns Finding enum with result. (6) Record: findings become observations via record_daemon_observation(live, finding) with agent=braid:daemon, confidence=0.99 (filesystem facts are certain), category=structural-finding. (7) Reflect: call calibrate_phrasing_patterns(live) to update pattern weights from recent hypothesis outcomes. (8) Prepare: update a cached DaemonInsights struct: { structural_findings: Vec<Finding>, pending_semantic_hypotheses: Vec<BridgeHypothesis>, phrasing_accuracy: BTreeMap<Pattern, f64> }. (9) Surface: when agent requests braid status, prepend daemon insights: 'Since last session: N structural investigations, M findings. Top finding: parser has 0 tests. Semantic hypotheses: ...' ACCEPTANCE: (A) Daemon with 5+ observations runs cognitive_tick and produces structural findings. (B) FileExists check correctly identifies present/absent files. (C) ImportCheck correctly detects import statements in Go/Rust/Python/JS files. (D) TestCoverage correctly counts test files per package. (E) Findings appear as observations in store with agent=braid:daemon. (F) Structural findings appear in braid status output. (G) cognitive_tick completes in <500ms per tick. (H) Zero regression in existing daemon tests. DEPENDS-ON: CE-CONN, CE-TEMP. FILE: crates/braid/src/daemon.rs (cognitive_tick + investigate_structural + StructuralCheck + Finding)"
